# ---- data: NOTHING under data/ gets committed ----
# (raw dumps, the parquet dataset, derived counts, reference caches -
#  all of it is regenerable via the scripts/notebooks)
# NOTE: 'data/*' (not 'data/') so git still DESCENDS into data/ and lets the
# reference-cache whitelist below take effect (a bare 'data/' blocks re-includes).
data/*
# keep only the documentation/placeholder files so a fresh clone
# still shows the expected folder structure:
!data/README.md
!data/processed/README.md
!data/raw/PUT_DATA_HERE.txt

# EXCEPTION: the reference cache the WORK LAPTOP needs for the live append
# (aggregate_posts looks up the ticker universe + word-ticker screening here).
# These are public Nasdaq symbol lists + a DERIVED case-ratio table - they hold
# NO post text, authors or ids, so they are safe to commit. The re-include-dir-
# then-re-exclude-contents pattern keeps the seen-ids ledger (a .json) private.
!data/reference/
data/reference/*
!data/reference/nasdaqlisted.txt
!data/reference/otherlisted.txt
!data/reference/ticker_classification.csv

# ---- GIC_RAW_DATA: the ONE data folder we DO commit ----
# It holds only the five abstracted aggregates (daily counts + sentiment
# scores per ticker/theme) - NO post text, authors, ids or subreddits. See
# GIC_RAW_DATA/README.md. Belt-and-suspenders: never let raw text or the
# local dedup ledger slip in even if a file lands here by mistake.
GIC_RAW_DATA/*.jsonl
GIC_RAW_DATA/*.zst
GIC_RAW_DATA/*.json
GIC_RAW_DATA/posts*.parquet
GIC_RAW_DATA/*slice*.parquet
# (the live seen-ids ledger lives at data/reference/gic_live_meta.json, which
#  is already ignored by the data/ rule above - post ids stay private.)

# secrets - NEVER commit credentials
curl.txt

# junk / regenerable
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.DS_Store
.venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.bak
*.bak.parquet
